<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Everton have agreed to sign Abdoulaye Doucoure from Watford for a fee of around £20million.</p>

<p>The 27-year-old will travel to Merseyside to undergo his medical in the next 48 hours.</p>

<p>Everton are overseeing a rebuild of their midfield in this transfer window, with James Rodriguez and Allan also close to joining the club.</p>

<p>Everton have agreed to sign Abdoulaye Doucoure from Watford for a fee of around £20m</p>

<p>Rodriguez is set to join from Real Madrid for over £20million, while Allan is on the verge of signing from Napoli for £21million, meaning Everton will have spent around £65million on improving their midfield.</p>

<p>Doucoure was eager to remain in the Premier League following Watford's relegation to the Championship. </p>

<p>Carlo Ancelotti is overseeing a significant rebuild at Everton as the club improve their midfield</p>

<p>Colombia midfielder James Rodriguez is expected to arrive from Real Madrid for over £20m</p>

<p>Allan is set to join Everton from Napoli for £20m as the club continue their recruitment drive</p>

<p>The Frenchman possesses plenty of Premier League experience having made 129 appearances in the division for Watford.</p>

<p>Doucoure's ability to drive forward from midfield is a useful asset and the arrival of Rodriguez will also bolster Everton's creativity. </p>

<p>Earlier in the transfer window Everton secured a deal for left-back Niels Nkounkou, who was previously at Marseille.</p>
